#nexus [SplitsTree6]

BEGIN SPLITSTREE6;
DIMENSIONS nDataNodes=10 nAlgorithms=6;
PROGRAM version='SplitsTree App (version 6.3.20, built 16 May 2024)';
WORKFLOW creationDate='1771517761900'; [Thu Feb 19 16:16:01 UTC 2026]
END; [SPLITSTREE6]

[
Methods:
Analysis was performed using SplitsTree CE 6.0.0 (Huson and Bryant 2006).
The original input consisted of 51 taxa and 51 Standard sequences of length 20,480.
The P Distance method (Hamming 1950) was used (default options) so as to obtain a 51 x 51 editDistance matrix.
The Neighbor Net method (Bryant & Moulton 2004, Bryant & Huson 2023) was used (default options) so as to obtain 158 splits, cyclic.
The Delta Score method (Holland et al 2002) was used so as to obtain an analysis result.
The Show Splits method was used (default options) so as to obtain a Split Network visualization.

References:
Bryant & Huson 2023: D. Bryant and DH Huson, NeighborNet- improved algorithms and implementation. Front. Bioinform. 3, 2023.
Bryant & Moulton 2004: D. Bryant and V. Moulton. Neighbor-net: An agglomerative method for the construction of phylogenetic networks. Molecular Biology and Evolution, 21(2):255– 265, 2004.
Hamming 1950: Hamming, Richard W. Error detecting and error correcting codes. Bell System Technical Journal. 29 (2): 147–160. MR 0035935, 1950.
Holland et al 2002: BR Holland, KT Huber, AWM Dress and V. Moulton, Delta Plots: A tool for analyzing phylogenetic editDistance data, Molecular Biology and Evolution, 19(12):2051–2059, 2002.
Huson and Bryant 2006: D.H. Huson and D. Bryant. Application of phylogenetic networks in evolutionary studies. Molecular Biology and Evolution, 23:254–267, 2006.
]

